FBIS4-59087 "drnes091_j_94038" FBIS-NES-94-091 Daily Report 9 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Reports of Arab League's Plan To Visit Denied Reports of Arab League's Plan To Visit Denied JN0905054494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0440 GMT 9 May 94 JN0905054494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Foreign Minister brother Muhammad Salim Basindwah has denied radio and news agency reports that an Arab League delegation will arrive in Sanaa to mediate a cease-fire. The brother foreign minister objected to the Arab League meeting to discuss an internal Yemeni affair, viewing such a meeting as a serious precedent that could extend to other Arab countries in the future. The brother foreign minister emphasized that what is taking place in Yemen is just a confrontation by the legitimate authorities of a rebel group that has deviated from constitutional legitimacy.
